# Model Cache Management API

## Overview

The SDK provides APIs to query and manage the model cache:
- Check if models are cached on disk
- Check if models are loaded in memory
- Get model metadata and status
- Download models explicitly
- Manage model lifecycle (load/unload)

## getModelInfo API

Returns comprehensive model status including cache state, loaded instances, and complete metadata.

### Parameters

```typescript
{
  name: string; // Unique model name from catalog (e.g., "WHISPER_TINY")
}
```

### Response

```typescript
{
  // Catalog metadata
  name: string;
  modelId: string;
  registryPath?: string;
  registrySource?: string;
  blobCoreKey?: string;
  blobBlockOffset?: number;
  blobBlockLength?: number;
  blobByteOffset?: number;
  engine?: string;
  quantization?: string;
  params?: string;
  expectedSize: number;
  sha256Checksum: string;
  addon: "llm" | "whisper" | "parakeet" | "embeddings" | "nmt" | "vad" | "tts" | "ocr" | "other";

  // Cache status
  isCached: boolean;
  cacheFiles: Array<{
    filename: string;
    path: string;
    expectedSize: number;
    sha256Checksum: string;
    isCached: boolean;
    actualSize?: number;
    cachedAt?: Date;
  }>;
  actualSize?: number;
  cachedAt?: Date;

  // Loaded status
  isLoaded: boolean;
  loadedInstances?: Array<{
    registryId: string;
    loadedAt: Date;
    config?: unknown;
  }>;
}
```

**Note:** `cacheFiles` is always an array:
- **Single-file models**: Array with 1 element containing the model file
- **Sharded models**: Array with multiple elements (one per shard file)
- Each element tracks its own cache status, size, and path

### Matching Logic

When identifying loaded instances, `getModelInfo` uses a two-tier matching strategy:

1. **Name matching** (preferred) - If registry entry has a `name`, compare with requested name
2. **Path matching** (fallback) - If no name match, compare with first cache file path

This ensures accurate identification when models are loaded using object-based constants.

**Implementation:**

```typescript
// server/rpc/handlers/get-model-info.ts
const loadedInstances: LoadedInstance[] = [];
for (const id of loadedModelIds) {
  const entry = getModelEntry(id);
  if (!entry?.local) continue;

  const matchesByName = entry.local.name && entry.local.name === name;
  const matchesByPath = cacheFiles.length > 0 && entry.local.path === cacheFiles[0]?.path;

  if (matchesByName || matchesByPath) {
    loadedInstances.push({
      registryId: id,
      loadedAt: entry.local.loadedAt,
      config: entry.local.config,
    });
  }
}
```

### Usage Example

```typescript
import { WHISPER_TINY } from "sdk";
import { getModelInfo } from "sdk";

// Single-file model
const info = await getModelInfo(WHISPER_TINY);
console.log("Model:", info.name);
console.log("Is cached:", info.isCached);
console.log("Cache files:", info.cacheFiles.length); // 1 for single-file models
console.log("Path:", info.cacheFiles[0]?.path);

// Sharded model
const shardedInfo = await getModelInfo({ name: "LLAMA_3_2_1B_INST_Q4_0_SHARD" });
console.log("Cache files:", shardedInfo.cacheFiles.length); // Multiple for sharded models
for (const file of shardedInfo.cacheFiles) {
  console.log(`${file.filename}: ${file.isCached ? "cached" : "missing"} - ${file.path}`);
}

// Check if all files are cached
if (info.isCached) {
  console.log("Total size:", info.actualSize);
  console.log("Latest cached at:", info.cachedAt);
}

// Check loaded instances
if (info.isLoaded) {
  console.log("Loaded instances:", info.loadedInstances?.length);
  info.loadedInstances?.forEach((instance) => {
    console.log("  Registry ID:", instance.registryId);
    console.log("  Loaded at:", instance.loadedAt);
  });
}
```

## downloadAsset API

Explicitly download a model to cache without loading it into memory.

### Parameters

```typescript
{
  assetSrc: string | ModelConstant; // Model source (string or object with src)
  seed?: boolean;                   // Enable hyperdrive seeding (default: false)
  onProgress?: (progress: ModelProgressUpdate) => void;
}
```

### Response

```typescript
{
  type: "downloadAsset";
  success: boolean;
  assetId?: string;
  error?: string;
}
```

The client API returns `Promise<string>` (the `assetId`), throwing on failure.

### Progress Updates

When `onProgress` is provided, the client uses streaming and receives `ModelProgressUpdate` events:

```typescript
{
  type: "modelProgress";
  downloaded: number;
  total: number;
  percentage: number;
  downloadKey: string;
  shardInfo?: {
    currentShard: number;
    totalShards: number;
    shardName: string;
    overallDownloaded: number;
    overallTotal: number;
    overallPercentage: number;
  };
  onnxInfo?: {
    currentFile: string;
    fileIndex: number;
    totalFiles: number;
    overallDownloaded: number;
    overallTotal: number;
    overallPercentage: number;
  };
}
```

### Usage Example

```typescript
import { WHISPER_TINY } from "sdk";
import { downloadAsset } from "sdk";

// Download with progress tracking
await downloadAsset({
  assetSrc: WHISPER_TINY,
  onProgress: (progress) => {
    console.log(`Progress: ${progress.percentage}%`);
    console.log(`Downloaded: ${progress.downloaded} / ${progress.total} bytes`);
  },
});

console.log("Model downloaded to cache");
```

## loadModel API

Load a model into memory. Will download if not cached.

### Parameters

```typescript
{
  modelSrc: string | ModelConstant;
  modelType: "llm" | "whisper" | "parakeet" | "embeddings" | "nmt" | "tts" | "ocr"
           | "llamacpp-completion" | "whispercpp-transcription" | "parakeet-transcription"
           | "llamacpp-embedding" | "nmtcpp-translation" | "onnx-tts" | "onnx-ocr"
           | string; // custom plugin types also accepted
  modelConfig?: { ... }; // model-type-specific config
  seed?: boolean;
  delegate?: DelegateConfig;
  onProgress?: (progress: ModelProgressUpdate) => void;
}
```

### Response

```typescript
{
  type: "loadModel";
  success: boolean;
  modelId?: string;
  error?: string;
}
```

### Usage Example

```typescript
import { WHISPER_TINY } from "sdk";
import { loadModel } from "sdk";

const modelId = await loadModel({
  modelSrc: WHISPER_TINY,
  modelType: "whisper",
});

console.log("Model loaded with ID:", modelId);
```

## unloadModel API

Unload a model from memory.

### Parameters

```typescript
{
  modelId: string;          // Registry ID from loadModel
  clearStorage?: boolean;   // Delete cached files (default: false)
}
```

### Response

```typescript
{
  type: "unloadModel";
  success: boolean;
  error?: string;
  hasActiveModels?: boolean;
  hasActiveProviders?: boolean;
}
```

### Usage Example

```typescript
import { unloadModel } from "sdk";

await unloadModel({ modelId });
console.log("Model unloaded from memory");
```

## Complete Workflow Example

```typescript
import { WHISPER_TINY } from "sdk";
import {
  getModelInfo,
  downloadAsset,
  loadModel,
  unloadModel
} from "sdk";

try {
  // 1. Check initial status
  const initialInfo = await getModelInfo(WHISPER_TINY);
  console.log("Is cached:", initialInfo.isCached);
  console.log("Is loaded:", initialInfo.isLoaded);

  // 2. Download if not cached
  if (!initialInfo.isCached) {
    await downloadAsset({
      assetSrc: WHISPER_TINY,
      onProgress: (p) => console.log(`  ${p.percentage}% complete`)
    });
  }

  // 3. Load if not loaded
  let modelId: string;
  const beforeLoad = await getModelInfo(WHISPER_TINY);

  if (!beforeLoad.isLoaded) {
    modelId = await loadModel({
      modelSrc: WHISPER_TINY,
      modelType: "whisper",
    });
  } else {
    modelId = beforeLoad.loadedInstances![0].registryId;
  }

  // 4. Use model for inference...

  // 5. Unload when done
  await unloadModel({ modelId });

  // 6. Verify final status
  const finalInfo = await getModelInfo(WHISPER_TINY);
  console.log("Is cached:", finalInfo.isCached); // true (still on disk)
  console.log("Is loaded:", finalInfo.isLoaded); // false (removed from memory)

  process.exit(0);
} catch (error) {
  console.error("Error:", error);
  process.exit(1);
}
```

## Cache Directory Structure

Models are cached in the configured cache directory (default: `~/.qvac/models/`):

```
~/.qvac/models/
  ├── a1b2c3d_model.gguf        # Cached model file
  ├── e4f5g6h_whisper-tiny.bin   # Another cached model
  └── ...
```

**File naming:** `{shortHash}_{modelId}`
- `shortHash` - Short hash of the `registryPath`
- `modelId` - Original model filename

## Cache States

A model can be in one of four states:

| State | `isCached` | `isLoaded` | Description |
|-------|------------|------------|-------------|
| **Not Downloaded** | `false` | `false` | Model not on disk, not in memory |
| **Cached** | `true` | `false` | Model on disk, not in memory |
| **Loaded** | `true` | `true` | Model on disk and in memory |
| **Memory Only** | `false` | `true` | Model in memory (loaded from non-cache source)* |

*\*Rare case when model is loaded from a source that doesn't use the cache directory*

## Cache Management Best Practices

### 1. Check Before Download

```typescript
const info = await getModelInfo(WHISPER_TINY);
if (!info.isCached) {
  await downloadAsset({ assetSrc: WHISPER_TINY });
}
```

### 2. Reuse Loaded Instances

```typescript
const info = await getModelInfo(WHISPER_TINY);
let modelId: string;

if (info.isLoaded) {
  modelId = info.loadedInstances![0].registryId;
} else {
  modelId = await loadModel({ modelSrc: WHISPER_TINY, modelType: "whisper" });
}
```

### 3. Unload When Done

```typescript
try {
  const modelId = await loadModel({ modelSrc: WHISPER_TINY, modelType: "whisper" });

  // Use model...

} finally {
  await unloadModel({ modelId });
}
```

### 4. Pre-download Models

```typescript
const modelsToPreload = [WHISPER_TINY, LLAMA_3_2_1B, EMBEDDINGGEMMA_300M_Q4_0];

await Promise.all(
  modelsToPreload.map(model =>
    downloadAsset({ assetSrc: model })
  )
);

console.log("All models pre-downloaded");
```

## Error Handling

```typescript
import { WHISPER_TINY } from "sdk";
import { getModelInfo } from "sdk";

try {
  const info = await getModelInfo(WHISPER_TINY);
  console.log(info);
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof Error) {
    if (error.message.includes("not found in catalog")) {
      console.error("Model not in catalog");
    } else {
      console.error("API error:", error.message);
    }
  }
}
```

